dice `los mandó llevar,´ <citebib id="Gideons"/> dice `los hizo 
pagar.´</rf></rb>
<t lang="es">. Se fue de Judea a Cesarea y allí se quedó. </t>
<sv num="20" id="Hechos-12-20"/>
Now Herod was very angry with the people of Tyre and Sidon. They came
with one accord to him, and, having made Blastus, the king´s chamberlain,
their friend, they asked for peace, because their country depended on the
king´s country for food. 
